ğŸ—‚ï¸ 1. Backup Script
âœ… Script:
#!/bin/bash
SOURCE="/home/ubuntu/aditya"
DESTINATION="/home/ubuntu/jaiswal/"
DATE=$(date +%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M-%S)

mkdir -p $DESTINATION/$DATE
cp -r $SOURCE $DESTINATION/$DATE
echo "Backup completed on $DATE"
ğŸ§  Explanation:
â€¢	SOURCE: Path to the directory you want to back up.
â€¢	DESTINATION: Where the backup should be stored.
â€¢	DATE: Captures the current time to create a timestamped backup folder.
â€¢	mkdir -p: Ensures the destination directory exists.
â€¢	cp -r: Recursively copies all files and folders.
â€¢	echo: Confirms the backup success with a timestamp.
ğŸ•’ Automation with Cron:
* * * * * /path/to/backup_script.sh
(Runs every minute. Modify for daily/hourly schedules.)
