ğŸ’½ 2. Disk Usage Check Script
âœ… Script:
#!/bin/bash
THRESHOLD=80
df -H | grep -vE '^Filesystem|tmpfs|cdrom' | awk '{ print $5 " " $1 }' |
while read output; do
  usage=$(echo $output | awk '{ print $1}' | cut -d'%' -f1)
  partition=$(echo $output | awk '{ print $2 }')
  if [ $usage -ge $THRESHOLD ]; then
    echo "Warning: Disk usage on $partition is at ${usage}%"
  fi
done
ğŸ§  Explanation:
â€¢	df -H: Shows disk usage in human-readable form.
â€¢	Filters out irrelevant lines (tmpfs, cdrom, etc.).
â€¢	Extracts %usage and device name.
â€¢	Checks if usage is above 80%.
â€¢	Sends a warning if threshold is crossed.
