ğŸ›¢ï¸ 5. MySQL Database Backup Script
âœ… Setup:
sudo apt install mysql-server
Login and set password:
ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'root';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
âœ… Script:
#!/bin/bash
DB_NAME="mydatabase"
BACKUP_DIR="/path/to/backup"
DATE=$(date +%Y-%m-%d_%H-%M-%S)

mysqldump -u root -p $DB_NAME > $BACKUP_DIR/$DB_NAME-$DATE.sql
echo "Database backup completed: $BACKUP_DIR/$DB_NAME-$DATE.sql"
ğŸ§  Explanation:
â€¢	Uses mysqldump to export the database to an SQL file.
â€¢	Timestamp helps in maintaining versioned backups.
â€¢	Add to cron to automate nightly backups.
