ğŸŒ 9. HTTP Response Time Script
âœ… Script:
#!/bin/bash
URLS=("https://www.devopsshack.com/" "https://www.linkedin.com/")

for URL in "${URLS[@]}"; do
  RESPONSE_TIME=$(curl -o /dev/null -s -w '%{time_total}\n' $URL)
  echo "Response time for $URL: $RESPONSE_TIME seconds"
done
ğŸ§  Explanation:
â€¢	Measures how long it takes to load a website using curl.
â€¢	Ideal for performance monitoring and uptime checks.
